Implement a Python `@memoize` decorator that caches function results based on arguments. It should work with any combination of positional and keyword arguments.

Include this test code at the end:

@memoize
def fibonacci(n):
    if n < 2:
        return n
    return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2)

@memoize
def add(a, b=0):
    return a + b

print(fibonacci(10))
print(fibonacci(30))
print(add(3, b=4))
print(add(3, b=4))
print(add(1, 2))
